We have to be cautious with the the use of AI. In fact, AI does not "think". It is only able to give us the answer with the most likelihood to be understandable. It does not understand fact, or determinism.

It is completly "probabilistic". We should then not take in account what AI tell us with certainty. 
AI is like a good intern, with access to a lot of books, in a quick amount of time, but without any sens of logic. It can only give us answer with likelihood and a sense of being good. It is also excellent to pretend to know so we should be completly cautious with it.